text: Hi everyone! My name is Megan, I’m a content marketing manager at a SaaS in Chicago. Just switched jobs from general marketing and editorial managing after being in the health/fitness industry for 4 years - I’ve been in marketing for 7+ years. My job switch also provided me with the opportunity to be a manager - I have a team of 2 great content writers right now, which will likely grow into demand gen (so any new-manager advice is welcome!). I love travel and have a photography-heavy travel website on the side called Moderately Excited - which I heavily credit for allowing me to make the leap more completely into content marketing. Data-supported storytelling rules!! :nerd_face: Thanks for having me here.

text: Hey everyone my name is Jordan and I'm co-founder of <https://hoteltechreport.com/|Hotel Tech Report>, a platform that helps hotel owners and managers find the best software and tech tools to run their businesses.  We've bootstrapped the business to 200+ paying software clients ranging from startups to Fortune 500s over the last 2.5 years.  My background is in finance and hotel investing so I've pretty much learned SEO/content marketing on the job and am pumped to learn from everyone in this group.  When I started the business I was naive to think we wouldn't even need a blog (which is hilarious to think about in hindsight).  We really only started blogging in June of last year and have grown our audience to more than 40,000 monthly readers in a pretty niche demo.  I'm gunning for 100,000 by the 1 year anniversary of our blog. Happy to discuss content collabs with SaaS companies who want exposure into hotels/hospitality and always love tips on things we can be doing better.
